<!--Model-->
<div class="register_modal_container">
    <div class="register_modal_content">
        <button id="register_close" class="register_close">+</button>
        <h2 class="sign_up_title">Sign Up</h2>
        <p>Create an Ethical Eating account</p>
        <form>
            <fieldset class="form_fieldset">
                <div class="form_input">
                    <label class="first_name_label" for="first_name">First Name</label>
                    <label class="last_name_label" for="last_name">Last Name</label>
                    <div class="name_input_container">
                        <input type="text" name="first_name" id="first_name" value="" size="25" maxlength="35">
                        <div id="first_name_error" class="error_msg"></div> <!--Reserve space for error message-->
                    </div>
                    <div class="name_input_container">
                        <input type="text" name="last_name" id="last_name" value="" size="25" maxlength="35">
                        <div id="last_name_error" class="error_msg"></div> <!--Reserve space for error message-->
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="form_input">
                    <div>
                        <label for="username">Username</label>
                    </div>
                    <input type="text" name="username" id="user" value="" size="60" maxlength="35">
                    <div id="username_error" class="error_msg"></div> <!--Reserve space for error message-->
                </div>
                <div class="form_input">
                    <div>
                        <label for="email">Email</label>
                    </div>
                    <input type="email" name="email" id="email" value="" size="60" maxlength="35">
                    <div id="email_error" class="error_msg"></div> <!--Reserve space for error message-->
                </div>
                <div class="form_input">
                    <div>
                        <label for="password">Password</label>
                        <span class="password_req">(6 or more alphanumeric characters)</span>
                    </div>
                    <input type="password" name="password" id="pass" value="" size="60" maxlength="35">
                    <div id="password_error" class="error_msg"></div> <!--Reserve space for error message-->
                </div>
                <div class="form_input">
                    <div>
                        <label for="confirm_password">Confirm Password</label>
                    </div>
                    <input type="password" name="confirm_password" id="confirm_password" value="" size="60" maxlength="35">
                    <div id="confirm_password_error" class="error_msg"></div> <!--Reserve space for error message-->
                </div>
                <div class="form_submit">
                    <button id="create_account_button" type="submit">Create Account</button>
                </div>
            </fieldset>
        </form>
    </div>
    <div class="success_modal_content">
        <div class="success_msg_container">
            <h2 class="success_msg">Account Created</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="close_msg_container">
            <button id="success_msg_close" class="success_msg_close">Close</button>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<!--End Model-->

<body>
    <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

    <h2>What is Ethical Eating?</h2>

    <div class = answer>
        Ethical Eating is all about helping you make more educated decisions about your food. We aim to inform you about the impact of such choices on the community,
        animals and the environment so that you can strive to reach the best conclusion for you. After all, we believe that every positive effort made on these issues 
        is important and worthwile.
    </div>

    <h2>Can I look up recipes using this website?</h2>

    <div class = answer>
        Yes! You can view available recipes by first selecting a meal category from the homepage. From there, simply click on a recipe of your choice to view its
        common ingredients.
    </div>

    <h2>How do I build my own recipe?</h2>

    <div class = answer>
        From the navbar, click on "Build a Recipe". Here, you are given a list of ingredients available to add to your custom recipe. Click the "Add" button to add the
        selected ingredient to your custom recipe on the left. You can always remove ingredients from your custom recipe even after you have added them.

    </div>

    <h2>How do I find out more information about each ingredient?</h2>

    <div class = answer>
        You can view more information about individual ingredients in the "Build a Recipe" page by clicking the "Info" button next to your ingredient of choice. The
        ingredient name, the issue associated with the ingredient, and any available alternatives for the selected ingredient will populate on the section to the right
        of the ingredient.
    </div>

    <h2>How do I save a recipe for later viewing?</h2>

    <div class = answer>
        You must be logged in to your account to save a recipe for later viewing. To register for a new account, click on "Register" from any page. You will be prompted
        to fill out a form and submit it. Once you have succesfully created an account, you will be able to log in and save a recipe from the "Build a Recipe" page.
    </div>
</body>
